.TH "account_locked_vm" 9 "account_locked_vm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
account_locked_vm \- account locked pages to an mm's locked_vm
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" account_locked_vm
.BI "(struct mm_struct *mm "  ","
.BI "unsigned long pages "  ","
.BI "bool inc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mm" 12
mm to account against, may be NULL
.IP "pages" 12
number of pages to account
.IP "inc" 12
true if \fIpages\fP should be considered positive, false if not
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Assumes a non-NULL \fImm\fP is valid (i.e. at least one reference on it).
.SH "RETURN"
* 0       on success, or if mm is NULL
* -ENOMEM if RLIMIT_MEMLOCK would be exceeded.
